About Us

Anna Poluektova is a college student who is working towards becoming a Computer Programmer Analyst and who will be graduating with her Diploma in April of 2015 from George Brown College in Toronto. From there, she hopes to be accepted into the Department of Computer Science at Ryerson University in Toronto. Anna hopes to work in Web Programming Industry.

In high school, Anna’s activities were to participate in schools and city’s Olympiads. Anna was a constant name on the honor roll and graduated from High School # 10 with a Silver Medal. Outside of the school she also participated in math and language competitions, so she ranked third on Soros Olympiad.

When she is not participating in classes at school, Anna enjoys spending her time solving math problems and helping her friends with their difficulties in math.
